    {
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "A vertex may be influenced by one or more joints. The skinned position of that vertex is defined",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "by a set of MeshJointInfluence values whose weights sum to 1. The skinned position is given by:",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code": [
            "position = vertexPosition(transformedByJoint: influences[0].jointIndex) * influences[0].weight",
            "         + vertexPosition(transformedByJoint: influences[1].jointIndex) * influences[1].weight",
            "         + ..."
          ],
          "syntax": "swift",
          "type": "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "The skinned position of a vertex is a linear combination of the vertex’s position transformed by",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "each joint, with weights given by the MeshJointInfluence values.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "To transform a vertex position by a joint, the initial vertex position is first transformed by",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "the joint’s inverse bind pose matrix, then by the local-to-parent transform of the joint, and",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "finally by the local-to-parent transform of each of the joint’s parents.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
  ],
